            <p>
            My SCM Story
            <br/>Good day beloved,  the story of my Christian journey is incomplete  without SCM UI where the seed of my salvation was watered, nourished and ever since has been growing. My encounter with the fellowship  started around this time 29 yrs ago when I got admission to UI. At the admission office area some brethren gave me a  handbill (not printed but hand written ) inviting me for a fellowship, some days later, on getting to my allocated room in idia hall, I was welcomed by a lovely Sister full of smiles in person of sis Tundun Ogunbanwo nee Fasina. She was very nice,  she was just like a big sister always ready to give a helping hand,  so automatically, when she invited me for a fellowship I couldn’t say no & when I asked her the name of the fellowship lo & behold it was the same with the handbill scm.
            <br/>The fellowship was full of life; it was as if all the brethren were taught how to smile and welcome people. Though they were not much, no musical instrument but you could feel the love,  feel at home with the brethren & also feel the presence of God. SCM UI was home away from home.
